On arrival the paramedics found that the taxi had rolled on its side.According to reports, it is believed that the 12 pupils are aged between 15 and 18.ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring ER24 said two pupils sustained serious injuries while ten others had injuries ranging from minor to serious.The less serious patients were treated on the scene, while the critically injured were provided with advanced life support interventions.&#8220;One of the critically injured boys was airlifted by the ER24 Oneplan helicopter while the second boy was airlifted by another private helicopter. Both boys are being treated at the nearby hospitals,&#8221; Meiring said.The other patients were transported by ambulance to various hospitals in the area.The cause of the collision is not yet known.-TNA Reporter 